CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1953, pg. 14 reads: "The Inter-Denominational Council of Church Nurses...recently held its second annual convention at Bethel AME Church with Mrs. Grace Barbour, president, presiding over the sessions. The council has $400 of $3,000 which it hopes to have in February, 1954, toward its objective of a home for delinquent boys and girls.  The three men on the picture are the REvs. Vernon Simpson, A.A. Hughey, host pastor, and E.P.Tunie, moderator of the Allegheny Union Baptist Association. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nurses, three men including Rev. Vernon Simpson, Rev. Andrew A.Hughey, and Rev. E. P. Tunie, with Grace Barbour wearing fur stole, posed in Bethel AME Church church for the Inter-Denominational Council of Church Nurses annual convention
